-- Spanish Bond Trading Fell 10% in June to 40 Billion Euros a Day
-- B y   P a u l   D o b s o n
-- 2012-07-27T12:36:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-27/spanish-bond-trading-fell-10-in-june-to-40-billion-euros-a-day.html
Spain ’s government bond trading fell
10 percent to an average 40.1 billion euros a day in June, from
44.7 billion euros a day the previous month, according to a
document on the website of the nation’s Treasury.  On an annual basis, the last time trading volumes were that
low was in 1997, the data show.  To contact the reporter on this story:
